00:24:42.719 --> 00:24:52.239
is using RMD to use officer to create PowerPoint and Word presentations, so you can be

00:24:52.239 --> 00:25:00.560
interested by those packages. And lastly, about PDF documents, if you really want that,

00:25:00.560 --> 00:25:06.479
because you need to produce some report and send them in PDF, it's often not easy,

00:25:08.000 --> 00:25:14.640
because producing PDF, the main usage is using LaTeX, and so as I said, when you want to style

00:25:14.640 --> 00:25:22.319
an output, you need to style it by the technology that is used to create it, so PDF will be created

00:25:22.319 --> 00:25:30.800
by LaTeX, and you need to use LaTeX to style the document, so there is some specific LaTeX

00:25:30.800 --> 00:25:39.599
packages that you can use, sometimes it could be helpful if you already played with articles

00:25:39.599 --> 00:25:46.719
package, or if you've already written LaTeX, you know about that, if you don't, maybe it's not

00:25:46.719 --> 00:25:53.359
as important to invest in it, because there is a new way to create PDF, it is through HTML,

00:25:53.359 --> 00:26:00.160
and the good news is that you can use CSS in that case, so you can use the same technology

00:26:00.160 --> 00:26:06.560
to produce the HTML and to produce the PDF, and there is two solutions to create PDFs for HTML,

00:26:06.560 --> 00:26:12.800
the first one is kind of simple one, is printing the document as is, it means like if you are

00:26:12.800 --> 00:26:19.040
using Chrome for example, there is a good printing function, but the drawback is that it will print

00:26:19.040 --> 00:26:26.479
the document as you see on the screen, so usually a web page is linear, it can be very long,

00:26:26.479 --> 00:26:32.239
and it can be not suited to be printed on A4 formats or paginated documents,

00:26:33.199 --> 00:26:38.239
but the second solution is to format and style the HTML specifically for printing

00:26:39.040 --> 00:26:45.760
a document to PDF or to a paginated format using what is called page media CSS,

00:26:46.719 --> 00:26:51.119
and the good news is that there is an R package for that, which is called PageDone,

00:26:51.119 --> 00:26:55.760
I won't give much example, I just wanted to share that with you in case you don't know about it,

00:26:56.800 --> 00:27:03.599
PageDone will allow you to create paginated HTML, and it brings basically, it brings a

00:27:03.599 --> 00:27:14.160
page.js JavaScript library to R, which is used to create paginated content, so by paginated I mean

00:27:14.160 --> 00:27:20.160
that when you will open the HTML on the screen, it will look like some pages that you can see,

00:27:20.160 --> 00:27:27.359
and the pages is defined by margin, is defined by header, footer, a page number usually,

00:27:27.359 --> 00:27:34.560
a running header, something like that, so you can really create paginated content using HTML,

00:27:34.560 --> 00:27:40.959
and if you are interested, I would suggest that you look at the talk by Yui Hsieh on RStudio Conf

00:27:40.959 --> 00:27:53.040
2019, which was where PageDone was announced. As an example, I wanted to show you this, so what

00:27:53.040 --> 00:28:00.239
you can see on the left is the resulting document that you can create using PageDone, so this

00:28:00.239 --> 00:28:08.640
document is created using PageReport, which is a community package developed by Thomas Roland and

00:28:08.640 --> 00:28:16.479
David Case, and they wanted to simplify the use of PageDone through templates, because PageDone

00:28:16.479 --> 00:28:25.280
is really the core tools to customize, but there is some templates included in it, but if you want

00:28:25.280 --> 00:28:30.400
to make a template specific to your organization that looks like that, it could be a good amount

00:28:30.400 --> 00:28:35.359
of work, and what they did is provide templates where you can change some parts of the template,

00:28:35.359 --> 00:28:42.640
look at the colors, the fonts, the cover, or the logo, so it can be a good way to start with

00:28:43.520 --> 00:28:49.199
this and as examples to see how you can create such templates.

