That was a lot of information, so we've seen how to customize HTML output

00:29:01.920 --> 00:29:07.599
using different technology, we've seen how to use templates, mainly with Office outputs,

00:29:08.400 --> 00:29:14.079
we've seen that you can create custom parts in your document using margin syntax,

00:29:14.640 --> 00:29:22.800
specific margin syntax, and we've seen that PDF can also be customized for your organization

00:29:22.800 --> 00:29:30.160
if needed. What you need to remember is that this is just the beginning, for some time there

00:29:30.160 --> 00:29:35.760
was no easy solution, CSS was the only one for HTML, recently it's easier through the use of

00:29:35.839 --> 00:29:41.439
SAS and BSLib, and hopefully it will be easier in the years to come, because we are working

00:29:42.000 --> 00:29:47.119
