Aaron, I see you had some feedback there on most email servers will not display JavaScript.

00:52:14.560 --> 00:52:20.639
Yeah. Yeah, that's my experience. I think the suggestion of using Blastula to do a JPEG is

00:52:20.959 --> 00:52:25.199
you can attach an HTML file, but somebody will have to open a browser, which is hard on their phone.

00:52:29.439 --> 00:52:32.239
The right way to do that is probably to link to something

00:52:33.040 --> 00:52:37.520
elsewhere, and then use a JPEG via Blastula to get stuff captured.

00:52:40.399 --> 00:52:42.399
Thank you. Hi, Aaron. Nice to see you.

00:52:42.959 --> 00:52:43.459
Hi.

00:52:46.000 --> 00:52:52.719
Another question. We have maybe time for three more. What would be the right best practices

00:52:52.719 --> 00:52:57.280
to follow while creating business reports in PowerPoint using R Markdown?

00:52:58.239 --> 00:53:07.679
You can do that using R Markdown. You need to keep a simple report because there is not a lot

00:53:07.679 --> 00:53:13.120
of customization that you can do. Usually, when you are doing a PowerPoint slide in PowerPoint

00:53:13.120 --> 00:53:20.639
manually, you would do a lot of tweaks, eventually, placeholders, and so on, but you don't have to do

00:53:21.439 --> 00:53:26.959
a PowerPoint slide in PowerPoint manually. You would do a lot of tweaks, eventually,

00:53:26.959 --> 00:53:33.280
place components in different places. When you are using a tool like R Markdown to create those,

00:53:33.280 --> 00:53:42.800
you will need to keep a fixed layout on things, like have three to four template slides, like one

00:53:42.800 --> 00:53:47.919
main slide, main layout, or two-part layout, things like that, and stay with that in the

00:53:47.919 --> 00:53:55.600
whole presentation, and try to keep it simple. Basically, this is also something that we are

00:53:55.600 --> 00:54:03.199
interested in feedback from because it may not be as easy to do that. We have improved during the

00:54:03.199 --> 00:54:10.479
summer, as I said, working with someone from the Pandoc team, so it won't work as best as it should

00:54:10.479 --> 00:54:20.639
right now, but it will hopefully come soon into that. The best practice would be keep it simple

00:54:20.639 --> 00:54:25.280
in your slide, but it's something that is not just for PowerPoint output, I guess.

00:54:27.199 --> 00:54:32.959
I know I like to tweak a lot of things and to style a lot of things, so I prefer HTML presentation

00:54:34.080 --> 00:54:38.560
and often print them to PDF if I need to send them to someone else.

00:54:41.120 --> 00:54:46.159
Thank you, Christophe. There are two other questions left around PDFs.

00:54:47.520 --> 00:54:53.199
So, one is, to print PDFs using PageZone, you need to use a Chromium-based browser.

00:54:53.919 --> 00:54:59.120
Can you print multiple dynamic reports using PDF print, using Shiny?

00:55:00.719 --> 00:55:02.959
And, Chris, feel free to add any context, too.

00:55:02.959 --> 00:55:14.080
Yeah, you can print PDF using PageZone with any tool that allows you to print HTML

00:55:14.080 --> 00:55:20.000
and that supports the page media rules. You need to use a Chromium-based browser because

00:55:22.000 --> 00:55:32.719
Chromium has a function and has an API that allows us to dynamically call a print on documents. So,

00:55:32.719 --> 00:55:39.120
in PageZone, you have a function that is called Chrome underscore print that will basically open

00:55:39.120 --> 00:55:48.800
Chrome or Edge, load the document, and then print this. But if you have other technology,

00:55:48.800 --> 00:55:55.439
like the previous technology was PhantomJS, but it's deprecated now, but there are surely other,

00:55:55.439 --> 00:56:02.159
I guess you can do that. And from Shiny, you would be able to do that for dynamic report, but

00:56:03.040 --> 00:56:08.080
you need to have the external tool available. So, you need to have Chromium or you need to have this

00:56:08.080 --> 00:56:15.120
tool available in the Shiny app or in the server so that you can call them. But you can print

00:56:15.120 --> 00:56:22.239
dynamically HTML to PDF using those kind of tools. So, you should be able to do that in the Shiny

00:56:22.239 --> 00:56:27.600
app also. Depends after on which server you are deploying your application.

00:56:28.560 --> 00:56:35.199
Okay. And on a similar thought, someone just asked, will PDF produce via CSS

00:56:35.199 --> 00:56:40.000
and PageJS give me the same level of control as a LaTeX template?

00:56:42.320 --> 00:56:50.239
It depends how much you know about LaTeX, I guess. If someone is using LaTeX from like 10 years or

00:56:50.239 --> 00:56:57.360
more, he will know a lot about how to use LaTeX template and style. And I think it can do a lot

00:56:57.360 --> 00:57:05.679
of things and PageJS and CSS can be a hard step for such person. But if you don't know LaTeX yet,

00:57:05.679 --> 00:57:14.000
maybe more interested to invest into CSS and PageJS because it could be more toward the future.

00:57:14.000 --> 00:57:22.639
And HTML, you can do a lot of things and it's really powerful, but it could rely on a lot of

00:57:22.719 --> 00:57:29.520
high skill. But I see the same for LaTeX. Like I know only basic about LaTeX and I won't be,

00:57:29.520 --> 00:57:34.320
I know I'm not able to make a LaTeX template and I think I will be able to make a HTML template.

00:57:34.320 --> 00:57:42.639
So, I would say yes, you can do that. But PageJS is kind of new and it's still new for the web and

00:57:42.639 --> 00:57:51.280
LaTeX is here since a very long time and is made for doing PDF and doing papers and things like

00:57:51.280 --> 00:57:57.360
that. So, I guess you can do more using LaTeX now if you know about it and if it works well for you.

